2025-12-31 21:23:35,545 - MetaFlow.llm.client - INFO - Execute tool write_file with args: {'path': 'core/movement.py', 'content': 'from typing import Tuple\n\nclass Movement:\n    """\n    Handles the movement logic for the snake, including direction changes.\n    """\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def change_direction(current_direction: Tuple[int, int], new_direction: Tuple[int, int]) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n        """\n        Changes the snake\'s direction, ensuring it does not reverse.\n\n        :param current_direction: The current direction of the snake as a (dx, dy) tuple.\n        :param new_direction: The new direction to change to as a (dx, dy) tuple.\n        :return: The updated direction as a (dx, dy) tuple.\n        """\n        # Prevent reversing direction (e.g., going from (1, 0) to (-1, 0))\n        if (current_direction[0] + new_direction[0] == 0 and \n            current_direction[1] + new_direction[1] == 0):\n            return current_direction\n\n        # If valid, return the new direction\n        return new_direction'}
