2025-12-31 21:25:13,662 - MetaFlow.llm.client - INFO - Execute tool write_file with args: {'path': 'core/map_loader.py', 'content': 'import json\nimport os\nfrom typing import List, Tuple\nfrom config import MAP_DIRECTORY\n\nclass MapLoader:\n    """\n    A class responsible for loading map configurations from JSON files.\n    """\n\n    def load_map(self, map_name: str) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n        """\n        Loads the specified map configuration and returns wall coordinates.\n\n        Args:\n            map_name (str): The name of the map file to load (without path).\n\n        Returns:\n            List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of (x, y) tuples representing wall coordinates.\n        """\n        # Construct the full path to the map file\n        map_path = os.path.join(MAP_DIRECTORY, map_name)\n\n        try:\n            # Open and load the map file\n            with open(map_path, \'r\') as file:\n                map_data = json.load(file)\n\n            # Extract and return wall coordinates\n            return map_data.get("walls", [])\n        except (FileNotFoundError, json.JSONDecodeError):\n            # Return an empty list if the file is missing or invalid\n            return []'}
