2025-12-31 21:27:10,620 - MetaFlow.llm.client - INFO - Execute tool write_file with args: {'path': 'core/map_loader.py', 'content': 'import os\nimport json\nfrom typing import List, Tuple\nfrom config import MAP_DIRECTORY\n\nclass MapLoader:\n    """Loads map configurations from JSON files."""\n\n    def load_map(self, map_name: str) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n        """\n        Loads the specified map configuration and returns wall coordinates.\n\n        Args:\n            map_name (str): The name of the map file to load.\n\n        Returns:\n            List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of wall coordinates from the map.\n\n        Raises:\n            FileNotFoundError: If the map file does not exist.\n            ValueError: If the map file is improperly formatted.\n        """\n        map_path = os.path.join(MAP_DIRECTORY, f"{map_name}.json")\n\n        if not os.path.exists(map_path):\n            raise FileNotFoundError(f"Map file \'{map_name}\' not found in directory \'{MAP_DIRECTORY}\'.")\n\n        with open(map_path, \'r\') as file:\n            try:\n                map_data = json.load(file)\n            except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n                raise ValueError(f"Failed to parse map file \'{map_name}\': {e}")\n\n        # Validate map structure\n        if "walls" not in map_data or not isinstance(map_data["walls"], list):\n            raise ValueError(f"Map file \'{map_name}\' is missing \'walls\' or has an invalid format.")\n\n        # Ensure all wall coordinates are tuples of two integers\n        walls = []\n        for coord in map_data["walls"]:\n            if not (isinstance(coord, list) and len(coord) == 2 and all(isinstance(x, int) for x in coord)):\n                raise ValueError(f"Invalid wall coordinate format in map \'{map_name}\': {coord}")\n            walls.append(tuple(coord))\n\n        return walls'}
